# TODO.5 — Frame Sampling Node

## Objective

Implement `src/frame_sample.py` — extract keyframes from video using three strategies.

## Tasks

1. Implement `run(config: JobConfig, segments: list[ASRSegment]) -> list[SampledFrame]`:
   - Strategy 1: Fixed interval sampling (every N seconds, default 3s)
   - Strategy 2: Scene-change detection (ffmpeg `select='gt(scene,0.3)'`)
   - Strategy 3: Low-confidence ASR region sampling (denser frames around flagged segments)
   - Deduplicate frames that are too close in time (within 0.5s)
   - Save frames to `{output_dir}/{job_id}/frames/`
   - Each SampledFrame records: frame_path, timestamp, sample_reason
2. Write `tests/test_frame_sample.py`:
   - Mock ffmpeg subprocess
   - Test each sampling strategy independently
   - Test deduplication logic
   - Test frame naming convention

## Acceptance Criteria

- Frames saved with sequential naming: `frame_000001.jpg`, etc.
- Each frame has timestamp and reason recorded
- Near-duplicate timestamps deduplicated
- Tests pass without ffmpeg

## Dependencies

- TODO.1, TODO.4 (needs ASR segments for low-confidence sampling)
